Poulin attended St. Francis College in Maine where he received a B.A. in 1960. He continued his studies in literature at Loyola University in Chicago, where he earned an M.A. in 1960. Poulin attended the University of Iowa between 1966 and 1968 ultimately obtaining an M.F.A. in poetry (his thesis was 
               In Advent: Poems and Translations
            ).
